						<summary>

						<p>South wall of the Bṛihatkaruṇāmbikā shrine in the same temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">[Sundara-pāṇḍyadēva]: Year 32,</hi><note n="124-1">The year has been read as 22 in <hi rend="italic">A.R.S.I.E.,</hi> 1909.</note><hi rend="bold">Chittirai = 1297-98 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription is damaged. It records an endowment of 45 <hi rend="italic">paṇam,</hi> of which 35 <hi rend="italic">paṇam</hi> was for providing food offerings and 10 <hi rend="italic">paṇam</hi> was for the procession of the image of the deity (name lost), probably of the temple of Avināśi Āḷuḍaiyār. The name of the donor is lost but it seems that he hailed from Māḍakkuḷakkīḻ-Madurai (i.e., Madurai) in [Pāṇḍi]-maṇḍalam.</p>						

						</summary>
